- Based on your comments, I added a test caseï¼š
@Test
    public void test005(){
        AsciiString ascii = new AsciiString("12345678910");
        int b = ascii.lastIndexOf("6");
        System.out.println(b);

    }
   But the result is still -1, this is not what I expected.In my opinion, this should return 5.

   I looked at the source code,

   public int lastIndexOf(CharSequence string) {
   // Use count instead of count - 1 so lastIndexOf("") answers count
   return lastIndexOf(string, length());
   }

   lastIndexOf(string, length()) should be modified to lastIndexOf(string, 0) ?
